<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/805.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                        Japan</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In answer to invitation to participate in Chinese loan transmitted in
                                your March 11, The Minister for Foreign Affairs expresses
                                appreciation of condition that equal participation be tendered Japan
                                and Russia and undertakes on behalf of his Government to join in
                                said <pb facs="0231" n="115" xml:id="pg_115"/> loan, designating the
                                Yokohama Specie Bank as the representative of the Japanese financial
                                group.</p>
                            <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs adds: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>The Imperial Government naturally expect that nothing
                                        connected with the projected loan will operate to the
                                        prejudice of the special rights and interests of Japan in
                                        the region of southern Manchuria.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>